column37: Kevin, Seth, Nichele, Munis, Teddie, & Brandon
column38: We rode the shoal creek route. It was my first actual time riding at all! I feel good about riding. Brandon helped me with shifting gears and understanding how they work and why we change them.

I know the miles won't count but I really wanted to ride today! We were supposed to ride Shoal with Sujata and Anne but we quickly realized it would have been dangerous for Anne to be out on the road. Ulrika and I would trade off teaching Anne skills and riding a loop with Sujata (we were at a parking lot in front of some fields on the Great Northern Rd on the route). In all, I did just 3 loops and helped Anne with Skills.

column22: Brandon Ortiz, Ashley Wallace, Sierra Welch
column23: We did the East route, but we had to turn around a couple miles early because it was going to get dark. Things were communicated very well. Brandon was a great ride leader. All good things!

column18: We road the Shoal Creek route. It was extremely foggy and the roads were pretty slick. I also had an exam, so we had to stop a bit shy of 20 miles, but I still wanted to let you guys know that we rode!
column38: So cold, but great ride on Shoal Creek!

column23: We rode the Shoal Creek ride. It was extremely windy and cold and that slowed up down a bit.
column38: Great ride on Shoal Creek. :)

column18: I rode with Haley at Shoral Creek at 7 am. It was Haley's first time riding that long and she wasn't super confident at first so we actually drove out to Shoral creek and started the ride there. I led the ride at 12 mph and we were only able to completed 17 miles. It was a great ride and we both felt great during and after the ride. However, we were not able to reach 20 miles because the weather (foggy, drizzling, misty, and slick road) and Haley had an exam that morning too.
column38: The ride was a little bit tough towards the end because of how cold it was. My fingers and toes were hurting so bad. They hurt each time I unclipped and stopped. Otherwise, it wasn't too bad of a ride. :)
Shoal Creek; Vanessa & Ulrika traded off riding loops with me and helping Anne with skills in the little league fields' parking lot

column37: Seth, Kevin, Brandon, Nichele, Teddie, Sunshine
column38:
Biked to Shoal Creek, 2x loop, and a couple miles of wrong turns and getting lost

Generally, things were communicated well. There was a range of skills and fitness levels, so there were frequently large gaps riders. 

I was concerned about stop signs. People generally stopped, but it seemed that the attitude was that the ride leader would stop at first and give the all clear, and then everyone was supposed to follow in a big group. So each person was not stopping individually at the stop sign. Maybe this is how it is supposed to be done.

column18: We did the Buda Taco route, which went through downtown and South first, neither of which have bike lanes. While I felt Jacob and I were comfortable enough, it is an unsafe route for beginners. We did stop for tacos for 30 minutes which was nice.

column38: We got lost. And then stopped. And rode around some neighborhoods for a while. 2 hours is not an accurate bike efficiency time for me; it'd be much lower. Was great. 10/10. Would ride again.

column37: Teddie, Munis, Kevin, Seth, Brandon, Sunshine, Emmy, Courtney, Mark
column38: Rode 24 miles with Kevin, Brandon, Seth, Sunshine, Teddie and Munis then caught up to Emmy, Courtney and Mark and continued with them. Did continuous loops of Shoal.

column18:
Buda Tacos route

Ride time includes a ~40 min taco stop

*** We were surprised that this route is approved so early in our training.  Most of it has no shoulder and moderate traffic.  We did fine, but it would be concerning to have novice riders attempting this ride. ***

column38:
Shoal Creek loop several times. Ride went really well, but was a very slow pace for my liking.  It was nice to be able to help Sunshine and Teddy feel more comfortable on the bike.  

I hope to pick up the pace with them next time.

column37: Brandon Ortiz, Seth Snyder, Munis Rashid, Nichele Newman, Sunshine Garrison, Teddie Owen
column38: We did the Shoal Creek loop a few times. It was a wonderful ride -- perfect weather for riding! Riding in a group of 7 was definitely challenging -- it was difficult to make sure that everyone stayed together -- but it was a lot of fun. We also had quite a few skill levels represented on the ride, ranging from experienced cyclists to someone's FIRST RIDE (yay Sunshine!), which proved to be challenging but rewarding. Overall great ride!

column38:
We did the Shoal Creek route, with adjustments, and it was definitely hard, but I had only done the training camp ride before, so I improved a lot. I'm still learning to communicate the right things at the right time as well as improving my shifting. 

Also, my bike computer isn't working right, so I'm not entirely sure the exact mileage we did, but it was definitely over 20 miles.
